  <description><![CDATA[<p>Base Camp offers a selection of studios and apartments in Cielo Alto with fresh furnishings and modern décor.</p>
<h2>Home From Home</h2>
<p>This self catering home-from-home accommodation offers a great environment to relax in, giving you the freedom to dine in <a data-udi="umb://document/bfccaf52eb4c47f09ae3657298234fda" href="/{localLink:umb://document/bfccaf52eb4c47f09ae3657298234fda}" title="Cervinia">Cervinia's</a> bars and restaurants or use the modern kitchen facilities to cook your own food.</p>
<h2>Dining Options</h2>
<p>The Base Camp restaurant is just a two minute walk away and offers continental breakfast and evening meal options which can be arranged and paid for locally. We recommend giving the pizzas here a try, they're delicious.</p>
<h2>Location</h2>
<p>There's a small shop nearby for all your essentials or you can take the resort bus that stops just outside the apartment and be at the large supermarket within five minutes.</p>
<p>The bus will also link you to the main lifts area, ski school and ski hire shop. If you don't fancy the bus, the bottom half of the Cieloalto red run is directly outside and links to Breuil-Cervinia, then it's about a three-minute walk to the main lift. It's also possible to ski right back to the apartments if the snow conditions are right.</p>]]></description>
